Package fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph

Interface Graph<N extends Node,​E extends Edge>

Type Parameters:
N - The Node subclass used to construct the graph
E - The Edge subclass used to construct the graph
All Superinterfaces:
EdgeSet<E>, NodeSet<N>, fr.cnrs.iees.omhtk.Textable
All Known Implementing Classes:
ALGraph
public interface Graph<N extends Node,​E extends Edge> extends NodeSet<N>, EdgeSet<E>, fr.cnrs.iees.omhtk.Textable

The root interface for graphs. Just as in the mathematical definition of a Graph G as G=(N,E,f) where N is a set of nodes and E a set of edges connecting the nodes, this interface extends the NodeSet and the EdgeSet interfaces.

A Graph depends on a GraphFactory to instantiate its components (implementations of Nodes and Edges). Therefore, constructors of implementing classes must always provide a factory as parameters.

Author:
Jacques Gignoux - 14 mai 2019
